MERRIAM SEABI (27) from Stinkwater, north of Tshwane, said her life is a mess because of her father&rsquo;s angry ancestors.She said her boyfriends keep leaving her and she cannot keep a job for more than two months. But she believes her luck will change if she meets Peter Tabane, her father.&ldquo;All I want is to meet his family so they can perform a ritual for me.&rdquo; She said a number of sangomas have told her she will not amount to anything until she finds her father.Elizabeth Seabi (47), Merriam&rsquo;s mum, said she met Peter in Winterveldt in 1988. &ldquo;A year later, I fell pregnant. After three months, he disappeared.&rdquo; She said Peter&rsquo;s older brother told her he saw Peter at Mabopane Station in 2014. &ldquo;This proves he is still in Tshwane.&rdquo;